<h1>BEZIER CURVES AND SURFACE OF REVOLUTION
</h1>
<h2>Naga Sai Sri. Kamineni, Prakruthi Burra and Vasudha.V</h2>
<h3>Bezier curve</h3>
<p>Bezier curve has been implemented using the recursive de Casteljau's algorithm. The curve was drawn pixel by pixel. We get to choose the degree of the curve by choosing the number of points to be given as inputs. After choosing the points, we use certain keys for other functions:</p>

<dl>
	<dt><b>'d'</b></dt>
	<dd>
		To draw the curve.
	</dd>
	
	<dt><b>'a'</b></dt>
	<dd>
		To add a new point. A new point is chosen after pressing 'a'. 'd' is pressed again to draw the new curve.
	</dd>
	<dt><b>'r'</b></dt>
	<dd>
		To remove point. The point to be deleted is chosen after pressing 'r', after which the curve is redrawn using 'd'.
	</dd>
	<dt><b>'m'</b></dt>
	<dd>
		To choose a point to drag around. The point is chosen after pressing 'm', after which the point is dragged around with the left mouse button held down.
	</dd>
	<dt><b>'s'</b></dt>
	<dd>
		To save the current curve to as .off format, so as to be viewed as a surface to revolution.
	</dd>
</dl>



